    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-09-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="416"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul-General <persName type="from">Steinhart</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-09-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 12, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State of the Republic of Cuba at 3.40 to-day delivered to me a
                    memorandum, in his own handwriting, a translation of which follows: “The
                    rebellion has increased in the provinces of Santa Clara, Habana, and Pinar del
                    Rio, and the Cuban Government has no elements to contend it, to defend the towns
                    and prevent the rebels from destroying property. President Estrada Palma asks
                    for American intervention, and begs that President Roosevelt send to Habana with
                    rapidity two or three thousand men to avoid any catastrophe in the capital. The
                    intervention asked for should not be made public until the American troops are
                    in Habana. The situation is grave and any delay may produce a massacre of
                    citizens in Habana.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhart</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                        >Consul-General</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
